olive oil
1 packet diced bacon
1 packet garlic paste
1 pinch chilli flakes
1 packet tomato sugo
½ bottle cream
½ sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet Fresh Fettuccine
1 apple
1 cucumber
1 bag spinach & rocket mix
1 bottle Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing
1 bag parsley
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Boil the kettle. Heat olive oil in a frying pan over high heat
• Cook bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 3 mins
• Add garlic paste and a pinch of chilli flakes (if using), cook until fragrant, 1 min
• Add tomato sugo, cream (1/2 packet for 2P / 1 packet for 4P) and seasoning (1/2 sachet for 2P / 1 sachet for 4P), cook until thickened, 2-3 mins

• Half-fill a saucepan with boiling water, place over high heat, then add a generous pinch of salt
• Bring to the boil, then add fettuccine and cook until ‘al dente’, 3 mins
• Transfer cooked fettuccine to frying pan with a dash of pasta water and toss to coat

• Thinly slice apple and cucumber
• In a bowl, combine apple, cucumber, spinach & rocket mix and dressing. Season to taste
• Divide bacon pasta between plates
• Top with Parmesan and torn parsley. Serve with apple salad